Washington 11-3 (AFP) - The American Defense Department said today, Tuesday, that Secretary William Cohen is confident of Saudi Arabia's support in the crisis between the United Nations and Iraq.
 
The Saudi Crown Prince received the American secretary in Riyadh, and they held talks on the crisis between Iraq and United Nations experts in the area of disarmament.
 
Defense Department Spokesman Kenneth Bacon said that "Secretary Cohen is confident after this meeting that the United States will get the support it needs to take appropriate measures to back the United Nations."

Cohen is due to arrive in Kuwait tomorrow, Wednesday, for a visit that lasts 24 hours. 